Hi Stephan,
A follow up question on the error message in 1.8:

Please Consider the following code:

---
import org.eclipse.jdt.annotation.Nullable;

class Y {
	void foo() { }
}
public class X {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      @Nullable Y value = computeY();
      value.foo();  // -->   Error
   }
   private static @Nullable Y computeY() { return null;  }
}
---

// Error
(1) For 1.8 the error message is:
Potential null pointer access: this expression has a '@Nullable' type
(2) For 1.7 the error message is:
Potential null pointer access: The variable value may be null at this location

Isn't the error message in 1.7 better that 1.8 ?
